yes, really strange. i guess i'm doing something the wrong way or something like that...

i added in layout.user.php following lines after the opening div

```
<div id="content">
<?php
// created this folder manually via ftp as 755
$extractdir = '/var/path-to-owncloud/temp/oc-5.0.13';
$archive = \oc_archive::open('/var/path-to-owncloud/temp/ultitest.tar.bz2');
if (!$archive){
      echo 'reading failed';
} else if (!$archive->extract($extractdir)) {
      echo 'extraction failed';
} else {
      echo "extraction completed!";
}
exit;
?>
```

doesn't matter what i put into my .tar.bz2 archive, it won't extract. always "extraction failed".

with one exception: if there is nothing in the archive except files with **long filenames** (> 100 or 120) like that one https://te-cloud.de/public.php?service=files&t=575cf9bb800a29e7f0141f8272cc9cb8
if you shorten the name to "lorem ipsum.txt" it won't extract. if you put other files or folders with short filenames into the archive it won't extract.

i also compared the version of 3rdparty>archive>tar.php with my version: it's exactly the same.

really don't understand what's going on here. additionally, i can't see how to get the exact error-message from the archive class?
